{{Infobox scientist |name = Gunnar Hoppe |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1914|12|24}} |birth_place = |death_date = {{death date and age|2005|01|24|1914|12|24|df=y}} |death_place = |residence = Sweden |citizenship = |nationality = Swedish |field = [[Quaternary geology]] |work_institutions = [[Stockholm University]] |alma_mater = |doctoral_advisor = |father = [[Carl Hoppe]] |known_for =[[Veiki moraine]] |influences = |influenced = |prizes = [[Swedish Society for Anthropology and Geography#Awards given by the society|Vega Medal]] <small>(1987)</small> |religion = |footnotes = |signature = }} '''Ernst Gunnar Hoppe''' was a [[Swedish people|Swedish]] [[geographer]] and [[Quaternary science|Quaternary]] [[geologist]]. He became a member of the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences]] in 1964. At ''Stockholms högskola'' (as [[Stockholm University]] was known before it was granted university status in 1960) he succeeded [[Hans Wilhelmsson Ahlmann]] as [[professor]] of [[geography]] in 1954, holding that position until 1980. He was rector of Stockholm University from 1974 to 1978. In 2004, he obtained an [[honorary doctorate]] from the [[University of Iceland]].<ref>{{cite web |title=The University of Iceland honorary degree recipients, 2000-2009 |url=http://english.hi.is/honorary_degrees/honorary_degrees |publisher=University of Iceland |accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref> Hoppe also was a member of the [[Bavarian Academy of Sciences and Humanities]],<ref>[http://www.badw.de/de/akademie/mitglieder/historisch/mitglied/index.html?per-id=1384 Verstorbene Mitglieder | Prof. Dr. Gunnar Hoppe] {{de icon}}</ref> the [[Academy of Sciences Leopoldina]],<ref>[http://www.leopoldina.org/en/members/list-of-members/member/3512/ List of Members | Gunnar Hoppe]</ref> [[Academia Europaea]]<ref>[http://www.ae-info.org/ae/User/Hoppe_Gunnar Former Members | Gunnar Hoppe]</ref> and the [[Polish Academy of Sciences]].<ref>[http://www.english.pan.pl/index.php/members/deceased-members Deceased Members]</ref>
