[[File:Zastupitelské úřady Abcházie.svg |thumb|right|450px|Map of diplomatic missions of Abkhazia {{legend|#ff0000|Abkhazia}} {{legend|#212178|Abkhaz embassy}} {{legend|#5f8dd3|Abkhaz representative office}} {{legend|#aaccff|Abkhaz embassy, non-resident}}]]
This page lists the '''diplomatic missions of [[Abkhazia]]'''. The Republic of Abkhazia is a [[List of states with limited recognition|state with limited recognition]], which declared independence from Georgia in 1999, but did not receive recognition from any [[Member states of the United Nations|UN member states]] until after the 2008 South Ossetia war. Abkhazia is recognized by [[Russia]], [[Nicaragua]], [[Venezuela]], [[Nauru]] and [[Syria]].  In addition, it is recognized also by [[Nagorno-Karabakh]], [[South Ossetia]], and [[Transnistria]], which are not members of the [[United Nations]]. Abkhazia has four embassies abroad and small network of representative offices in near countries. Abkhazia also has four honorary consulates.{{#tag:ref|There are honorary consuls based in [[China]] ([[Beijing]]), [[Russia]] ([[Nizhny Novgorod]], [[Rostov-on-Don]]) and [[United Kingdom]] ([[London]]). Honorary consul in United Kingdom is professor George Hewitt.<ref>{{cite web|title=George Hewitt |url=https://www.theguardian.com/profile/george-hewitt |website=The Guardian |date= |accessdate=2016-04-06}}</ref>|group="note"}}

