:''Not to be confused with [[Mount Thomas (Antarctica)]]

'''Thomas Mountains''' ({{coord|75|33|S|70|57|W|display=inline,title}}) is a separate cluster of rocky mountains, about 5 nautical miles (9&nbsp;km) long, standing 15 nautical miles (28&nbsp;km) northeast of [[Mount Horne]] in [[Palmer Land]]. Discovered by the [[Ronne Antarctic Research Expedition]] (RARE), 1947–48, under Ronne, who named these mountains for noted author and radio commentator [[Lowell Thomas]], a supporter of the expedition.

